summary:
So I’m rewatching Infinity War and you know what I just realized?
Tony had the phone Steve gave him WITH HIM.
Like, he didn’t...
body:
So I’m rewatching Infinity War and you know what I just realized?

Tony had the phone Steve gave him WITH HIM.

Like, he didn’t have to go get it, he didn’t have the number written down, he actually carried that phone around with him everywhere he went.

I’m crying.

summary: TV Review: Punisher S2E2 Fight or Flight
title: TV Review: Punisher S2E2 Fight or Flight
body:
Punisher S2E2 Fight or Flight isn’t bad but we’ve seen so much of it before in other shows and movies #netflix #marvel #thepunisher

Frank and a reluctant Rachel go on the run as a menacing adversary gives chase. Meanwhile, Madani pays Russo an unwelcome visit.

On the run and being pursued by bad guys, the episode is a typical one that we’ve seen so many times before. The victim doesn’t want to cooperate with the hero thinking he’s a bad guy. The hero makes a stand in a hotel and uses a second room (we’ve seen this one…

body:
Thanos: The problem with the world is that there is imbalance. There is too much life and not enough resources. If half of all life in the universe ceased to exist, the rest would be free to prosper. It's simple logic, really.
Us: Yes, but everyone would be sad because all their friends died.
